00:00:19,940 --> 00:00:20,680
got a leg up.

6
00:00:20,740 --> 00:00:21,880
So the method I'm going to teach you

7
00:00:21,880 --> 00:00:24,000
afterward will be even easier for you to

8
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:24,940
apply with options.

9
00:00:25,140 --> 00:00:26,400
Okay, here we go.

10
00:00:26,900 --> 00:00:29,280
So Susie's selling her house for $500,000

11
00:00:29,280 --> 00:00:31,400
in a neighborhood that has a nearby parcel

12
00:00:31,400 --> 00:00:33,880
of land that is for sale as well.

13
00:00:34,300 --> 00:00:36,160
There are two parties interested in the land.

14
00:00:36,160 --> 00:00:38,120
And Peter plans to develop the land into

15
00:00:38,120 --> 00:00:40,160
a beautiful park and bird sanctuary.

16
00:00:40,660 --> 00:00:43,020
And Harry plans to build a low-cost

17
00:00:43,020 --> 00:00:43,880
housing development.

18
00:00:44,320 --> 00:00:46,460
Now Sammy comes along and is interested in

19
00:00:46,460 --> 00:00:48,360
buying Susie's house for a cash deal.

20
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:49,720
But he has a problem.

21
00:00:50,200 --> 00:00:52,600
He won't have the cash available for three

22
00:00:52,600 --> 00:00:52,920
months.

23
00:00:53,240 --> 00:00:54,940
So he's of course worried that the house

24
00:00:54,940 --> 00:00:56,380
